"""Session 08 — register pia-flattened CZ to HCR vascular projections.

Pipeline:
  1. Compute pia-flattened projections at requested slab/mode for HCR
     channel `ch` and CZ. (uses :mod:`compute_projections` helpers).
  2. Warm-start: rotate CZ 180° and rescale by `sxy` (HCR-µm / CZ-µm,
     median bbox area ratio from `roi_area_sxy.estimate_sxy_roi_area`)
     so 1 CZ-pixel maps to (cz_xy_um · sxy) HCR-µm; then resample onto
     HCR-L4 pixel grid.
  3. Sweep small residual rotation θ ∈ [−30°, 30°] (coarse 2°, then
     fine ±2° at 0.25°) on the warm-started CZ template; for each θ,
     FFT-NCC against the HCR image to find best (tx, ty).
  4. Save overlay figures + JSON of best (θ, tx, ty, ncc) per variant.

Variants per subject (788406, 790322):
  V1: HCR ch561 [0,30] mean   ×  CZ [0,30] mean   (vasculature)
  V2: HCR ch488 [0,30] max    ×  CZ [0,30] max    (488 vs CZ)
  V3: HCR ch488 [0,100] max   ×  CZ [0,50] max    (deeper integration)
"""
